name: Report
summary:
The `{Report}` object in the Salesforce application is a structured entity used to store and manage data related to reports. It comprises various attributes that define its properties and metadata. Here's a summary of its attributes:

1. **Id (type: id)**: Unique identifier for the report.
2. **OwnerId (type: reference)**: Reference to the user who owns the report.
3. **FolderName (type: string)**: Name of the folder where the report is stored.
4. **CreatedDate (type: datetime)**: Date and time when the report was created.
5. **CreatedById (type: reference)**: Reference to the user who created the report.
6. **LastModifiedDate (type: datetime)**: Date and time when the report was last modified.
7. **LastModifiedById (type: reference)**: Reference to the user who last modified the report.
8. **IsDeleted (type: boolean)**: Indicates whether the report has been deleted.
9. **Name (type: string)**: Name of the report.
10. **Description (type: string)**: Description of the report.
11. **DeveloperName (type: string)**: Unique name used by developers to reference the report.
12. **NamespacePrefix (type: string)**: Prefix associated with the report, typically used in managed packages.
13. **LastRunDate (type: datetime)**: Date and time when the report was last run.
14. **SystemModstamp (type: datetime)**: System-generated timestamp for the last update.
15. **Format (type: picklist)**: Format of the report, chosen from predefined options.
16. **LastViewedDate (type: datetime)**: Date and time when the report was last viewed.
17. **LastReferencedDate (type: datetime)**: Date and time when the report was last referenced.

These attributes collectively define the report's identity, ownership, content, metadata, and usage history within the Salesforce environment.
label: Report
